                            <comment id="60649" author="jamesanunez" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2013 13:33:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed for 2.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="58140" author="jamesanunez" created="Fri, 10 May 2013 14:49:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proposed patch is at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,6313&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,6313&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An explanation of the problem is located in the comment section for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3304&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on sanity-quota test_18: watchdog triggered &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57590" author="jamesanunez" created="Thu, 2 May 2013 21:41:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The dmesg log you point to is from the OSS. Do we need to clear dmesg from all servers; OSS, MDS and MGS?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
James&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Update: Please ignore this questions. Looking at test 18, it&apos;s clear what server&apos;s dmesg is being queried.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56732" author="pjones" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 20:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;James&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please look into this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="56731" author="green" created="Mon, 22 Apr 2013 20:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_logs/ebe6ed72-a90d-11e2-85b9-52540035b04c/show_text&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_logs/ebe6ed72-a90d-11e2-85b9-52540035b04c/show_text&lt;/a&gt; has the story&lt;br/&gt;
the test picked up watchdog trigger from a previous run and so we need to clear the dmesg buffer at the start of the test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
